========================================================================
PART 4: GAUSS SUMS AND FIBONACCI
========================================================================

The QUADRATIC GAUSS SUM for p ≡ 1 mod 4:
  g(χ) = Σ_{a=0}^{p-1} (a/p) · e^{2πia/p} = √p

For p ≡ 3 mod 4:
  g(χ) = i√p

Our Fibonacci product uses sin(πk/p) = (ζ^k - ζ^{-k})/(2i)
where ζ = e^{πi/p}.

The JACOBI SUM: J(χ,χ) = Σ_{a+b≡1} χ(a)χ(b) = g(χ)²/g(χ²)

For the Legendre symbol χ = (·/p):
  J(χ,χ) = -1 + Σ_{a=1}^{p-1} χ(a)χ(1-a)

Can F_p be expressed as a Gauss/Jacobi sum?
F_p = (φ^p - ψ^p)/√5. Since φψ = -1:
  F_p = φ^p(1 - (ψ/φ)^p)/√5 = φ^p(1 - (-1)^p·φ^{-2p})/√5

For odd p: F_p = φ^p(1 + φ^{-2p})/√5 = (φ^p + φ^{-p}·(-1)^p)/√5...

Actually: F_p = (φ^p - ψ^p)/√5 with ψ = -1/φ:
  For odd p: ψ^p = -φ^{-p}, so F_p = (φ^p + φ^{-p})/√5

Wait: ψ = (1-√5)/2 ≈ -0.618.
ψ^p for odd p: |ψ|^p · (-1)^p = (-1)^p/φ^p

For odd p: ψ^p = -1/φ^p
So F_p = (φ^p + 1/φ^p)/√5 = L_p/√5... no that's wrong.

Actually φ - ψ = √5, φ + ψ = 1, φψ = -1.
F_n = (φ^n - ψ^n)/(φ - ψ) = (φ^n - ψ^n)/√5.
L_n = φ^n + ψ^n.

