SYNTHESIS: THE NUMBER-THEORETIC WEB
========================================================================

                    ┌──────────────────────┐
                    │   Q(√5) — the field   │
                    │   of golden ratio     │
                    └──────────┬───────────┘
                               │
        ┌──────────────────────┼──────────────────────┐
        │                      │                      │
   ┌────▼────┐          ┌─────▼─────┐          ┌─────▼─────┐
   │ Fibonacci│          │  Cassini   │          │  Dedekind  │
   │ F_p=prod │          │ Norm = -1  │          │ ζ_K(s)     │
   │ (1+Q_k)  │          │ Pentagon   │          │ Res = πR/√5│
   └────┬────┘          └─────┬─────┘          └─────┬─────┘
        │                      │                      │
        │    ┌────────────────┼────────────────┐     │
        │    │                │                │     │
   ┌────▼────▼──┐     ┌──────▼──────┐   ┌─────▼─────▼─┐
   │ Tournament  │     │ Ising model  │   │  L(1,χ₅)    │
   │ H = p·F·A  │     │ β·J = 2R     │   │  = π/√5     │
   │ = p·H₀     │     │ ξ = 1/(4R)   │   │  = πF_∞/φ^∞ │
   └─────────────┘     └──────────────┘   └─────────────┘

THE GOLDEN RATIO φ IS THE FUNDAMENTAL UNIT OF Q(√5).
Every quantity in our research is a power or function of this unit:
  F_p = Tr(φ^p) / √5                (Fibonacci = trace)
  L_{2m} = Tr(φ^{2m})               (Lucas = trace)
  H_from_0 = Tr(φ^p) · A(p) / √5   (H = trace × amplification)
  Cassini = Norm(φ^p) = -1           (Cassini = norm)
  Growth rate = log(φ) = Regulator   (asymptotic rate)
  Residue of ζ_K = πR/√5             (analytic class number formula)

